                    <div class="col-lg-3 col-md-3 instrument-box eq-blocks card">
                        <div class="ins-tr-wrapper card-body">
                            <h4 class="ins-title">Mini Chart Indicator</h4>
                            <div class="ins-desc">
                                No more switching between MT4 charts – see price action on multiple instruments and/or timeframes by just clicking and dragging to adjust the size of a sub-window chart inside the main one.
                                <br><br>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                        <div class="card-footer">
                        </div>
                    </div>
                    <div class="col-lg-3 col-md-3 instrument-box eq-blocks card">
                        <div class="ins-tr-wrapper card-body">
                            <h4 class="ins-title">Renko Bar Indicator</h4>
                            <div class="ins-desc">
                                Draw blocks on normal MT4 time-based charts for visibility over gaps in time frames and create offline charts with only Renko blocks, be they continuous or separated.
                                The indicator can also be used to create an offline MT4 chart containing only the Renko blocks – a more traditional Renko chart which is not time-based like a normal MT4 chart.
                                <br><br>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                        <div class="card-footer">
                        </div>
                    </div>
                    <div class="col-lg-3 col-md-3 instrument-box eq-blocks card">
                        <div class="ins-tr-wrapper card-body">
                            <h4 class="ins-title">High-Low Indicator</h4>
                            <div class="ins-desc">
                                Pick the number of bars and the timeframe to let the High-Low indicator show you the highs and lows on a chart. With multiple copies, you gain visibility over different levels and can even choose to look at open/close prices as well. If you prefer to check specific daily time ranges and receive alerts when a price breaches a historic lol or high, this indicator will allow you to do it.

                                <br><br>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                        <div class="card-footer">
                        </div>
                    </div>
                    <div class="col-lg-3 col-md-3 instrument-box eq-blocks card">
                        <div class="ins-tr-wrapper card-body">
                            <h4 class="ins-title">Freehand Drawing Indicator</h4>
                            <div class="ins-desc">
                                Mark and highlight events on MT4 charts for ongoing live webinars or distributing screenshots that would facilitate the process for your clients. You can draw freely with your mouse, customise colours with your keyboard, and always go a step back if things go south.

                                <br><br>


                            </div>
                        </div>
                        <div class="card-footer">
                        </div>
                    </div>
                    <div class="col-lg-3 col-md-3 instrument-box eq-blocks card">
                        <div class="ins-tr-wrapper card-body">
                            <h4 class="ins-title">Gravity Indicator</h4>
                            <div class="ins-desc">
                                Market activity gravitates around you for effortless monitoring of support and resistance areas based on previous price action when utilising the Gravity Indicator.
                                Stronger and weaker activities are colour-coded to show everything clearly.  You choose what to focus on - draw from the current time onwards with all price activity to date or set a specific start time to only view price movements you are looking for.

                                <br><br>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                        <div class="card-footer">
                        </div>
                    </div>
                    <div class="col-lg-3 col-md-3 instrument-box eq-blocks card">
                        <div class="ins-tr-wrapper card-body">
                            <h4 class="ins-title">Keltner Indicator</h4>
                            <div class="ins-desc">
                                Displays Keltner channels, similar to Bollinger® bands – the difference being in size, with channels being based on ATR instead of the standard deviation. If a price crosses a lower or upper channel, you can be alerted immediately.

                                <br><br>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                        <div class="card-footer">
                        </div>
                    </div>
                    <div class="col-lg-3 col-md-3 instrument-box eq-blocks card">
                        <div class="ins-tr-wrapper card-body">
                            <h4 class="ins-title">Linear Regression Indicator</h4>
                            <div class="ins-desc">
                                Plain and simple – you choose the number of N bars, the Linear Regression indicators show you a best-fit line through their close prices, highs, or lows. All three can be shown at a given time with multiple copies, forming a channel, and selecting different timelines gives you a broader choice of regression.

                                <br><br>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                        <div class="card-footer">
                        </div>
                    </div>
                    <div class="col-lg-3 col-md-3 instrument-box eq-blocks card">
                        <div class="ins-tr-wrapper card-body">
                            <h4 class="ins-title">Magnifier Indicator</h4>
                            <div class="ins-desc">
                                Select the bars you wish to see in detail from a lower timeframe and zoom in to them in a customisable sub-window. Drag the Magnifier and go around the chart, zooming in on any relevant historic periods.

                                <br><br>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                        <div class="card-footer">
                        </div>
                    </div>
                    <div class="col-lg-3 col-md-3 instrument-box eq-blocks card">
                        <div class="ins-tr-wrapper card-body">
                            <h4 class="ins-title">Order History Indicator</h4>
                            <div class="ins-desc">
